id: pm-22x2
title: "Search relevance evaluation harness (golden queries, nDCG) for regression detection"
description: No automated way to verify a ranking change improves/regresses quality. A golden-query fixture set scored via nDCG@5 gives a tuning feedback loop and catches regressions.
type: Task
status: in_progress
priority: 3
tags[6]: "area:search",eval,living-map,quality,roadmap,testing
created_at: "2026-05-31T19:44:24.148Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-06T07:52:19.485Z"
assignee: codex-search-eval-bundle
author: maintainer-agent
acceptance_criteria: "tests/search-eval/ JSON fixtures {query,mode,expected_top_ids}; pm test --eval-search (or pm reindex --eval) scores nDCG@5 with per-fixture pass/fail; optional non-blocking CI gate; seeded with 10-20 real corpus queries."
value: No automated way to verify a ranking change improves/regresses quality. A golden-query fixture set scored via nDCG@5 gives a tuning feedback loop and catches regressions.
parent: pm-ydp6
comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-06T07:16:54.484Z",codex-search-eval-bundle,"Kickoff: implementing package-owned reindex eval harness (pm reindex --eval) with golden-query fixtures and nDCG@5 scoring/output, plus contract/tests/docs updates in one combined PR with pm-fhsg."
  "2026-06-06T07:52:19.485Z",codex-search-eval-bundle,"Implementation complete: added package-owned reindex eval harness (--eval, --eval-fixtures) with fixture parsing/validation, per-query nDCG@5 scoring, pass/fail thresholds, aggregate summary, and deterministic JSON append under eval. Seeded default fixtures at tests/search-eval/golden-queries.json and documented fixture schema/usage in pm-search-advanced README. Verification evidence: focused tests (search-advanced runtime + release-readiness runtime) passed; contracts update/check passed; full coverage passed at 100/100/100/100. Manual temp-dir validation evidence: tmp_root=/tmp/tmp.0RrM2zV3ti, fixture_count=2, pass_count=2, fail_count=0, average_ndcg_at_5=1, passed=true. Both fixtures returned ndcg_at_5=1 and passed=true with per-fixture actual_top_ids emitted. PM validate check-resolution/check-history-drift and pm health --check-only both returned ok (validate includes existing resolution warnings unrelated to this change set)."
